<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.0011/17.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Emperor</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Great and Good Friend</hi>: I have received Your
                            Majesty’s letter of the 2d of August last, in which you conveyed to me
                            the sad tidings of the deaths on the 28th of June, of Your Majesty’s
                            dearly beloved nephew His Imperial and Royal Highness the Arch Duke
                            Franz Ferdinand and Her Highness the Duchess of Hohenberg.</p>
                        <p>I learn with deep sorrow of the great affliction which has befallen Your
                            Majesty and I offer to you my sincere and heartfelt condolences.</p>
                        <p>May God have Your Majesty and Your Majesty’s Family in His safe and holy
                            keeping.</p>
                        <p>Your Good Friend,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi></signed>. <lb/> By the
                            President: <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State</hi>. <lb/>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-20"><hi rend="italic">October 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>